text: I sent some notes on audio spectrum analysis to <@U030TQFR3> for review, and I've applied all the design feedback from Indah (except for updated help/about design which will be forthcoming from droga5 soon)

Happy to post it in the thread to andy if you think it's OK... as it turns out, FFT for audio spectrum analysis is fairly straightforward and shouldn't be hard to implement in our API, it just takes extra processing time, so the best approach would be to write a quick sample app (like the microphone amplitude demo) and see if the sample rate works well enough for the visualizations that experience authors might want to create
